    "SUMMARY": "Stade Municipal Saint-Symphorien is a multi-purpose stadium located on the \"island Saint-Symphorien\" in Longeville-lès-Metz, near Metz, France.  It is currently used mostly for football matches, by  Ligue 2 club FC Metz. The stadium is able to hold 30,000 people and was built in 1923."
